      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "The fruiting body is the mushroom you would recognize, and the mycelium is the root-like structure that grows underground. The active compounds most studied for cognitive support, hericenones and erinacines, are concentrated in the fruiting body. Many cheaper supplements use mycelium grown on grain, which dilutes the active compound content. DayShift uses an 8:1 concentrated fruiting body extract."
      }
    },
